The most important testimony in support of Nake's view is a passage in Att. ii. 1, 2, tu si tibi placuerit liber curabis ut et Athenis sit et in ceteris oppidis Graeciae, which shows clearly that Atticus was in the habit of actually publishing works of Cicero, the book here re- ferred to being a memoir of his consulship, written in Greek.
